===Etymology===
From a [[Hellenisation]] of earlier {{m|la|sulpur}}, from the root {{m|ine-pro|*selp-||fat, oil}}. Cognate with {{cog|en|salve}}, {{cog|sa|सर्पिस्||cleaned melted butter|tr=sarpís}}, {{m|sa|सृप्र||greasy, smooth|tr=sṛprá}}, {{cog|txb|ṣalype||ointment}}, and perhaps {{m|grc|ἔλπος||?olive oil, fat}} or {{cog|grc|ὄλπη||flask for oil}}.

According to De Vaan citing Szemerényi,<ref>{{R:itc:EDL}}</ref> perhaps from an s-stem {{der|la|ine-pro|*sélpos}}. However, De Vaan finds both the -él- > -ól- and -os > -ur changes to be irregular (for -ol- > -ul- see {{m|la|sulcus}}), adding that perhaps it comes from {{inh|la|itc-pro|*solpor}}, from an r/n-stem {{inh|la|ine-pro|*sólpr̥}} instead.

